{"title_page": "Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name          = Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1\n| image         =Petra Nemcova Cannes 2018 2.jpg \n| caption       =  N\u011bmcov\u00e1 at the [[2018 Cannes Film Festival]].\n| birth_name    = Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1979|6|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Karvin\u00e1]], [[Czechoslovakia]] (now [[Czech Republic]])\n| height        = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| haircolor     = Brown\n| eyecolor      = Hazel\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* Jonathan Sanders & Co (Worldwide)\n* One Management (New York)\n* Marilyn Agency (Paris)\n* View Management (Barcelona)\n* Place Models (Germany)\n* Next Models (Milan)\n* Stockholmsgruppen (Stockholm)<ref>https://models.com/models/Petra-Nemcova</ref> }}\n}}\n'''Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1''' ({{IPA-cs|\u02c8p\u025btra \u02c8\u0272\u025bmtsova\u02d0}}; born 24 June 1979) is a Czech [[fashion model|model]], television host and philanthropist who founded the ''Happy Hearts Fund''. In 2017, the ''Happy Hearts Fund'' merged with [[All Hands Volunteers]] to create [[All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]], with N\u011bmcov\u00e1 assuming the role of co-founder and vice chair.\n\n==Early life==\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 was born in [[Karvin\u00e1]],<ref name=\"FMDir\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Petra_Nemcova/|title=Petra Nemcova|work=The FMD - FashionModelDirectory.com}}</ref> then [[Czechoslovakia]], now the [[Czech Republic]], and grew up in Karvin\u00e1 in the [[Moravian-Silesian Region]] with her sister Olga.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Modeling===\nScouted on the streets of [[Prague]] by [[NEXT Model Management]], upon signing she moved to [[Milan]], Italy. After winning the 1995 Czech ''[[Elite Model Look]]'', she returned to Milan where her career flourished.\n\nShe has featured in campaigns for [[Benetton Group|Benetton]], [[Bulgari]], [[Cartier (jeweler)|Cartier]], [[Clarins]], Cortefiel, Dirk Bikkembergs, Fortunoff, Graff, [[Hewlett Packard]]/[[Intel]], HS, [[Intimissimi]], [[John Lewis (department store)|John Lewis]], Lancaster, [[La Perla (lingerie brand)|La Perla]], [[La Senza]], Maidenform, [[Max Factor]], Pantene Pro-V, Passport, [[Playtex]], Rampage, [[Schwarzkopf]], [[Victoria's Secret]], and Wild Orchid.<ref name=FMDir/> N\u011bmcov\u00e1 has appeared on international covers of ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Madame Figaro]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', ''Shape'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Flare (magazine)|Flare]]'', ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'', ''[[L'Officiel]]'', and ''Sports Illustrated''.<ref name=FMDir/>\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 has walked for designers including [[Lolita Lempicka]], Gai Mattiolo, [[Matthew Williamson]], Gugliemo Cappone, Marina Babini, Yumi Katsura, and [[Michiko Koshino]].<ref name=\"FMDir\"/>\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 gained attention outside the fashion industry after featuring on the cover of the 2003 [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' Swimsuit Issue]], from a shoot in [[Barbados]] by [[Walter Iooss]]. She also appeared in the 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005 and 2006 editions.<ref name=\"FMDir\"/> She was the object/subject of [[Joanne Gair]]'s [[body painting]] work.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/swimsuit/collection/issues/2004/04_pnemcova_08_bycategory.html|title=SI Swimsuit Collection: Petra Nemcova|accessdate=18 February 2008|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]}}</ref> In January 2015 N\u011bmcov\u00e1 replaced [[Abbey Clancy]] as the face of Ultimo underwear.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/swim-daily/2015/01/26/petra-nemcova-for-ultimo-photos-and-more-news|title=Petra Nemcova for Ultimo photos are out, and more news|author=Ultimo|work=SI.com}}</ref> She also serves as the global face of [[Chopard]]. \n\n===Television===\nIn 2001, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 appeared on British television series ''[[Absolutely Fabulous]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1023092/|title=Petra Nemcova|work=IMDb}}</ref> On 3 June 2004, she was one of the telecast judges during the 53rd annual [[Miss Universe]] competition in [[Quito]], Ecuador. In 2007, she was the host of TLC's ''[[A Model Life]]''. On 7 July 2007, she was a presenter at the [[Live Earth concert, New York City|American leg]] of [[Live Earth]].<ref name=\"FMDir\"/> N\u011bmcov\u00e1 was a contestant on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 12)|season 12]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' with dance partner [[Dmitry Chaplin]],  reaching the 4th week before being eliminated.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-31749_162-20038230-10391698.html | work=CBS News | first=Jessica | last=Derschowitz | title=\"Dancing with the Stars\" pairs revealed | date=2 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/dancing-with-stars-twelfth-season-partner-pairings-announced-12037.php|title='Dancing with the Stars' twelfth-season partner pairings announced|work=Reality TV World}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 published her autobiography ''Love Always, Petra'' ({{ISBN|0446579130}}).\n\n== 2004 Boxing Day tsunami ==\nOn 26 December 2004, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 was in [[Khao Lak]], [[Thailand]], with her main photographer and boyfriend, Simon Atlee, when the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]] struck.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/thailand/11303121/2004-Tsunami-Petra-Nemcova-the-supermodel-who-survived-the-Boxing-Day-tragedy.html \"2004 Tsunami: Petra Nemcova, the supermodel who survived the Boxing Day tragedy\"] Retrieved 11 June 2015.</ref> Atlee drowned and N\u011bmcov\u00e1 suffered a [[broken pelvis]] and serious internal injuries, but she managed to hold on to a [[palm tree]] for eight hours until she was rescued by Thai civilians and airlifted to an inland hospital nearby.<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Nemcova hospitalized with hip, internal injuries |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/news/story?id=1954697 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=29 December 2004 |accessdate=31 December 2008 |postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 serves on the advisory board of the Glamour's Women of the Year Fund.\n\nHer autobiography, ''Love Always, Petra,'' was released in 2005 from which 100% of the proceeds were donated towards helping children affected both by the 2004 tsunami in Thailand and ongoing natural disasters worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.petra-nemcova.com/-philantropist|title=petra-nemcova|website=petra-nemcova|language=ru|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n=== Happy Hearts Fund ===\nIn 2005, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 founded the [[Happy Hearts Fund]] (HHF), a charitable organization and campaign formed after the tsunami of 2004.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/petra-nemcova/restoring-the-lives-of-ch_b_399537.html | work=Huffington Post | first=Petra | last=Nemcova | title=Restoring the Lives of Children After Natural Disasters: How You Can Bring Happiness Back | date=18 March 2010}}</ref> \nThe main mission of Happy Hearts Fund has been  to rebuild and renew schools affected by natural disasters. As a result of programmes run by the Happy Hearts Fund, 176 schools have been rebuilt world-wide in 10 countries including [[Thailand]], [[Indonesia]], [[Haiti]], [[Nepal]], [[Peru]], [[Mexico]] and [[Philippines|The Philippines]]. N\u011bmcov\u00e1 has been heavily involved on an every day basis since establishing the Happy Hearts Fund, helping to establish long term strategies, as well as outlining the vision which has led to the organisations long term success. Her personal experience during the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami|2004 Boxing Day Tsunami]] gave her a deep understanding of the power of Mother Nature, allowing her to connect with those in need, bolstering the success of her work through the organisation. In late 2017, the Happy Hearts Fund merged with fellow non-profit organisation [[All Hands Volunteers]] to create [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]]. As a result, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 now acts as co-founder and vice chair of [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts]] alongside All Hands Volunteers founder [[David N. Campbell|David Campbell]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://happyheartsfund.org/world-impact/|title=World Impact - Happy Hearts Fund (HHF)|website=happyheartsfund.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n=== All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response ===\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 currently acts as co-founder and vice chair of [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]] (AHAH). \n\n[[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]] is a non-profit organisation dedicated to providing fast and effective support to communities hit by natural disasters worldwide. Amongst the first to respond and often to last to leave, All Hands And Hearts have helped to rebuild schools and homes across the globe, positively impacting over 105,000 children in disaster hit areas. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allhandsandhearts.org|title=All Hands and Hearts - Smart Response {{!}} Powered by Volunteers|website=All Hands and Hearts|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> The mission which N\u011bmcov\u00e1 outlined through the Happy Hearts Fund continues to be fulfilled by an international team of dedicated volunteers, to date numbering over 50,000, working in over 18 separate countries. N\u011bmcov\u00e1 herself has spoken about the importance of connecting with and understanding the needs of those in need of hope, empowerment and immediate aid, stating that, \"We cannot control nature, but we can control that actions that we take.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hands.org/team/petra-nemcova-copy/|title=Petra Nemcova {{!}} All Hands|work=All Hands|access-date=2018-06-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAs of June 2018, All Hands And Hearts has positively impacted over 1 million individuals affected by natural disasters, helping to rebuild 208 schools and hundreds of homes in over 95 different locations, spread across 18 individual countries. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allhandsandhearts.org|title=All Hands and Hearts - Smart Response {{!}} Powered by Volunteers|website=All Hands and Hearts|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> To date, 97 programmes have been launched in countries including [[Nepal]], [[Peru]], [[Mexico]], [[Japan]], [[Indonesia]] and the [[United States]].\n\n[[File:Petra Nemcova 2012 Shankbone.JPG|thumb|N\u011bmcov\u00e1 in 2012.]]\n\n=== Accolades ===\n''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'' magazine awarded N\u011bmcov\u00e1 a \"Survivor Award\" in 2005 for her charity work following her tsunami ordeal.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}\n\nIn June 2012, she was designated by president of Haiti [[Michel Martelly]] and Prime Minister Laurent Lamothe as Ambassador-at-Large for Haiti for her work with Happy Hearts Fund.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/model-petra-nemcovas-charity-work-in-haiti-honoured-7844905.html|title=Model Petra Nemcova's charity work in Haiti honoured|date=13 June 2012|work=The Independent}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Petra was appointed by the [[United Nations International Strategy for Disaster Reduction|UNISDR]] as a Disaster Risk Reduction Champion and Tsunami Awareness Advocate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unisdr.org/archive/55742|title=UN Appoints Tsunami Survivor as Global Advocate - UNISDR|website=www.unisdr.org|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 is [[multilingualism|multilingual]] and speaks [[Czech language|Czech]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Polish language|Polish]], English, French, and Italian. \n\nShe has been a [[vegan]] since 2007 and has paid close attention to life in the world's [[ocean]]s.<ref>[http://www.contactmusic.net/petra-nemcova/news/nemcova-becomes-a-vegan-in-a-bid-to-save-the-fish_1037959  ''Nemcova Becomes A Vegan In A Bid To Save The Fish.''], ''contactmusic.net'', 18.07.2007.</ref><ref>[https://www.peta.org/blog/supermodel-petra-nemcova-goes-vegan/  ''Supermodel Petra Nemcova Goes Vegan.''], ''peta.org'', 23.07.2007.</ref>\n\nShe was briefly engaged to English actor [[Jamie Belman]] before the couple ended their relationship in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1345105/Petra-Nemcova-engaged-British-actor-Jamie-Belman-whirlwind-month-romance.html|title=Petra Nemcova engaged to British actor Jamie Belman after whirlwind eight-month romance|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=7 January 2011|accessdate=7 January 2011|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20585983,00.html|title=Petra Nemcova and Jamie Belman Call Off Engagement|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=11 April 2012|accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 told ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' that she was dating the former [[Prime Minister of Haiti]], [[Laurent Lamothe]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Petra Nemcova: I'm 'Very Happy' Dating Laurent Lamothe|url=http://www.people.com/article/petra-nemcova-dating-laurent-lamothe}}</ref> but as of 2015 they were no longer together.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sontag|first1=Deborah|title=An Award for Bill Clinton Came With $500,000 for His Foundation|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/30/us/politics/an-award-for-bill-clinton-came-with-500000-for-his-foundation.html?referrer=&_r=0|accessdate=31 May 2015|work=Newspaper|publisher=The New York Times|date=29 May 2015}}</ref>  In 2017, she became engaged to investment banker Alejandro Grimaldi before the pair called off their engagement in December 2018.<ref>http://everything-pr.com/statement-from-petra-nemcova-and-alejandro-grimaldi/</ref>\n\nIn 2019, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 married French-Venezuelan entrepreneur Benjamin Larretche in [[Sedona, Arizona]]. They announced in September 2019 that they are expecting their first child.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Juneau |first1=Jen |last2=Leon |first2=Anya |title=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 Is Pregnant! Model, 40, Expecting First Child with Husband Benjamin Larretche |url=https://people.com/parents/petra-nemcova-pregnant-expecting-first-child-husband-benjamin-larretche/ |accessdate=20 September 2019 |magazine=People |date=September 19, 2019}}</ref> They welcomed their first child, a son, on November 15, 2019. He was born at 34 gestation and spent the first weeks of his life in the NICU.<ref> https://torontosun.com/entertainment/celebrity/supermodel-petra-nemcova-reveals-shes-a-new-mother-on-instagram/wcm/4ecda769-2333-46ea-b245-74dba0fceae3/amp</ref>\n\nSince 1997 Petra has had a cracking pair of tits.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |wikt=no |commons=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 |b=no |n=no |q=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 |s=no |v=no |species=no |display=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1}}\n*{{official website|http://www.petra-nemcova.com}}\n*{{Fashionmodel|name=Petra Nemcova}}\n*{{IMDb name|1023092|Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1}}\n\n{{SI Swimsuit Cover Models}}\n{{2000\u20132009 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nemcova, Petra}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Karvin\u00e1]]\n[[Category:Czech female models]]\n[[Category:Czech television personalities]]\n[[Category:Czech women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women writers]]\n[[Category:Czech philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in Italy]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name          = Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1\n| image         =Petra Nemcova Cannes 2018 2.jpg \n| caption       =  N\u011bmcov\u00e1 at the [[2018 Cannes Film Festival]].\n| birth_name    = Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1979|6|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Karvin\u00e1]], [[Czechoslovakia]] (now [[Czech Republic]])\n| height        = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| haircolor     = Brown\n| eyecolor      = Hazel\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* Jonathan Sanders & Co (Worldwide)\n* One Management (New York)\n* Marilyn Agency (Paris)\n* View Management (Barcelona)\n* Place Models (Germany)\n* Next Models (Milan)\n* Stockholmsgruppen (Stockholm)<ref>https://models.com/models/Petra-Nemcova</ref> }}\n}}\n'''Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1''' ({{IPA-cs|\u02c8p\u025btra \u02c8\u0272\u025bmtsova\u02d0}}; born 24 June 1979) is a Czech [[fashion model|model]], television host and philanthropist who founded the ''Happy Hearts Fund''. In 2017, the ''Happy Hearts Fund'' merged with [[All Hands Volunteers]] to create [[All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]], with N\u011bmcov\u00e1 assuming the role of co-founder and vice chair.\n\n==Early life==\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 was born in [[Karvin\u00e1]],<ref name=\"FMDir\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Petra_Nemcova/|title=Petra Nemcova|work=The FMD - FashionModelDirectory.com}}</ref> then [[Czechoslovakia]], now the [[Czech Republic]], and grew up in Karvin\u00e1 in the [[Moravian-Silesian Region]] with her sister Olga.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Modeling===\nScouted on the streets of [[Prague]] by [[NEXT Model Management]], upon signing she moved to [[Milan]], Italy. After winning the 1995 Czech ''[[Elite Model Look]]'', she returned to Milan where her career flourished.\n\nShe has featured in campaigns for [[Benetton Group|Benetton]], [[Bulgari]], [[Cartier (jeweler)|Cartier]], [[Clarins]], Cortefiel, Dirk Bikkembergs, Fortunoff, Graff, [[Hewlett Packard]]/[[Intel]], HS, [[Intimissimi]], [[John Lewis (department store)|John Lewis]], Lancaster, [[La Perla (lingerie brand)|La Perla]], [[La Senza]], Maidenform, [[Max Factor]], Pantene Pro-V, Passport, [[Playtex]], Rampage, [[Schwarzkopf]], [[Victoria's Secret]], and Wild Orchid.<ref name=FMDir/> N\u011bmcov\u00e1 has appeared on international covers of ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Madame Figaro]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', ''Shape'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Flare (magazine)|Flare]]'', ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'', ''[[L'Officiel]]'', and ''Sports Illustrated''.<ref name=FMDir/>\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 has walked for designers including [[Lolita Lempicka]], Gai Mattiolo, [[Matthew Williamson]], Gugliemo Cappone, Marina Babini, Yumi Katsura, and [[Michiko Koshino]].<ref name=\"FMDir\"/>\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 gained attention outside the fashion industry after featuring on the cover of the 2003 [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' Swimsuit Issue]], from a shoot in [[Barbados]] by [[Walter Iooss]]. She also appeared in the 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005 and 2006 editions.<ref name=\"FMDir\"/> She was the object/subject of [[Joanne Gair]]'s [[body painting]] work.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/swimsuit/collection/issues/2004/04_pnemcova_08_bycategory.html|title=SI Swimsuit Collection: Petra Nemcova|accessdate=18 February 2008|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]}}</ref> In January 2015 N\u011bmcov\u00e1 replaced [[Abbey Clancy]] as the face of Ultimo underwear.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/swim-daily/2015/01/26/petra-nemcova-for-ultimo-photos-and-more-news|title=Petra Nemcova for Ultimo photos are out, and more news|author=Ultimo|work=SI.com}}</ref> She also serves as the global face of [[Chopard]]. \n\n===Television===\nIn 2001, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 appeared on British television series ''[[Absolutely Fabulous]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1023092/|title=Petra Nemcova|work=IMDb}}</ref> On 3 June 2004, she was one of the telecast judges during the 53rd annual [[Miss Universe]] competition in [[Quito]], Ecuador. In 2007, she was the host of TLC's ''[[A Model Life]]''. On 7 July 2007, she was a presenter at the [[Live Earth concert, New York City|American leg]] of [[Live Earth]].<ref name=\"FMDir\"/> N\u011bmcov\u00e1 was a contestant on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 12)|season 12]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' with dance partner [[Dmitry Chaplin]],  reaching the 4th week before being eliminated.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-31749_162-20038230-10391698.html | work=CBS News | first=Jessica | last=Derschowitz | title=\"Dancing with the Stars\" pairs revealed | date=2 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/dancing-with-stars-twelfth-season-partner-pairings-announced-12037.php|title='Dancing with the Stars' twelfth-season partner pairings announced|work=Reality TV World}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 published her autobiography ''Love Always, Petra'' ({{ISBN|0446579130}}).\n\n== 2004 Boxing Day tsunami ==\nOn 26 December 2004, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 was in [[Khao Lak]], [[Thailand]], with her main photographer and boyfriend, Simon Atlee, when the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]] struck.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/thailand/11303121/2004-Tsunami-Petra-Nemcova-the-supermodel-who-survived-the-Boxing-Day-tragedy.html \"2004 Tsunami: Petra Nemcova, the supermodel who survived the Boxing Day tragedy\"] Retrieved 11 June 2015.</ref> Atlee drowned and N\u011bmcov\u00e1 suffered a [[broken pelvis]] and serious internal injuries, but she managed to hold on to a [[palm tree]] for eight hours until she was rescued by Thai civilians and airlifted to an inland hospital nearby.<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Nemcova hospitalized with hip, internal injuries |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/news/story?id=1954697 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=29 December 2004 |accessdate=31 December 2008 |postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\n\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 serves on the advisory board of the Glamour's Women of the Year Fund.\n\nHer autobiography, ''Love Always, Petra,'' was released in 2005 from which 100% of the proceeds were donated towards helping children affected both by the 2004 tsunami in Thailand and ongoing natural disasters worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.petra-nemcova.com/-philantropist|title=petra-nemcova|website=petra-nemcova|language=ru|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n=== Happy Hearts Fund ===\nIn 2005, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 founded the [[Happy Hearts Fund]] (HHF), a charitable organization and campaign formed after the tsunami of 2004.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/petra-nemcova/restoring-the-lives-of-ch_b_399537.html | work=Huffington Post | first=Petra | last=Nemcova | title=Restoring the Lives of Children After Natural Disasters: How You Can Bring Happiness Back | date=18 March 2010}}</ref> \nThe main mission of Happy Hearts Fund has been  to rebuild and renew schools affected by natural disasters. As a result of programmes run by the Happy Hearts Fund, 176 schools have been rebuilt world-wide in 10 countries including [[Thailand]], [[Indonesia]], [[Haiti]], [[Nepal]], [[Peru]], [[Mexico]] and [[Philippines|The Philippines]]. N\u011bmcov\u00e1 has been heavily involved on an every day basis since establishing the Happy Hearts Fund, helping to establish long term strategies, as well as outlining the vision which has led to the organisations long term success. Her personal experience during the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami|2004 Boxing Day Tsunami]] gave her a deep understanding of the power of Mother Nature, allowing her to connect with those in need, bolstering the success of her work through the organisation. In late 2017, the Happy Hearts Fund merged with fellow non-profit organisation [[All Hands Volunteers]] to create [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]]. As a result, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 now acts as co-founder and vice chair of [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts]] alongside All Hands Volunteers founder [[David N. Campbell|David Campbell]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://happyheartsfund.org/world-impact/|title=World Impact - Happy Hearts Fund (HHF)|website=happyheartsfund.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n=== All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response ===\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 currently acts as co-founder and vice chair of [[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]] (AHAH). \n\n[[All Hands Volunteers|All Hands And Hearts - Smart Response]] is a non-profit organisation dedicated to providing fast and effective support to communities hit by natural disasters worldwide. Amongst the first to respond and often to last to leave, All Hands And Hearts have helped to rebuild schools and homes across the globe, positively impacting over 105,000 children in disaster hit areas. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allhandsandhearts.org|title=All Hands and Hearts - Smart Response {{!}} Powered by Volunteers|website=All Hands and Hearts|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> The mission which N\u011bmcov\u00e1 outlined through the Happy Hearts Fund continues to be fulfilled by an international team of dedicated volunteers, to date numbering over 50,000, working in over 18 separate countries. N\u011bmcov\u00e1 herself has spoken about the importance of connecting with and understanding the needs of those in need of hope, empowerment and immediate aid, stating that, \"We cannot control nature, but we can control that actions that we take.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hands.org/team/petra-nemcova-copy/|title=Petra Nemcova {{!}} All Hands|work=All Hands|access-date=2018-06-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAs of June 2018, All Hands And Hearts has positively impacted over 1 million individuals affected by natural disasters, helping to rebuild 208 schools and hundreds of homes in over 95 different locations, spread across 18 individual countries. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allhandsandhearts.org|title=All Hands and Hearts - Smart Response {{!}} Powered by Volunteers|website=All Hands and Hearts|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> To date, 97 programmes have been launched in countries including [[Nepal]], [[Peru]], [[Mexico]], [[Japan]], [[Indonesia]] and the [[United States]].\n\n[[File:Petra Nemcova 2012 Shankbone.JPG|thumb|N\u011bmcov\u00e1 in 2012.]]\n\n=== Accolades ===\n''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'' magazine awarded N\u011bmcov\u00e1 a \"Survivor Award\" in 2005 for her charity work following her tsunami ordeal.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}\n\nIn June 2012, she was designated by president of Haiti [[Michel Martelly]] and Prime Minister Laurent Lamothe as Ambassador-at-Large for Haiti for her work with Happy Hearts Fund.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/model-petra-nemcovas-charity-work-in-haiti-honoured-7844905.html|title=Model Petra Nemcova's charity work in Haiti honoured|date=13 June 2012|work=The Independent}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Petra was appointed by the [[United Nations International Strategy for Disaster Reduction|UNISDR]] as a Disaster Risk Reduction Champion and Tsunami Awareness Advocate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unisdr.org/archive/55742|title=UN Appoints Tsunami Survivor as Global Advocate - UNISDR|website=www.unisdr.org|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nN\u011bmcov\u00e1 is [[multilingualism|multilingual]] and speaks [[Czech language|Czech]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Polish language|Polish]], English, French, and Italian. \n\nShe has been a [[vegan]] since 2007 and has paid close attention to life in the world's [[ocean]]s.<ref>[http://www.contactmusic.net/petra-nemcova/news/nemcova-becomes-a-vegan-in-a-bid-to-save-the-fish_1037959  ''Nemcova Becomes A Vegan In A Bid To Save The Fish.''], ''contactmusic.net'', 18.07.2007.</ref><ref>[https://www.peta.org/blog/supermodel-petra-nemcova-goes-vegan/  ''Supermodel Petra Nemcova Goes Vegan.''], ''peta.org'', 23.07.2007.</ref>\n\nShe was briefly engaged to English actor [[Jamie Belman]] before the couple ended their relationship in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1345105/Petra-Nemcova-engaged-British-actor-Jamie-Belman-whirlwind-month-romance.html|title=Petra Nemcova engaged to British actor Jamie Belman after whirlwind eight-month romance|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=7 January 2011|accessdate=7 January 2011|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20585983,00.html|title=Petra Nemcova and Jamie Belman Call Off Engagement|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=11 April 2012|accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 told ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' that she was dating the former [[Prime Minister of Haiti]], [[Laurent Lamothe]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Petra Nemcova: I'm 'Very Happy' Dating Laurent Lamothe|url=http://www.people.com/article/petra-nemcova-dating-laurent-lamothe}}</ref> but as of 2015 they were no longer together.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sontag|first1=Deborah|title=An Award for Bill Clinton Came With $500,000 for His Foundation|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/30/us/politics/an-award-for-bill-clinton-came-with-500000-for-his-foundation.html?referrer=&_r=0|accessdate=31 May 2015|work=Newspaper|publisher=The New York Times|date=29 May 2015}}</ref>  In 2017, she became engaged to investment banker Alejandro Grimaldi before the pair called off their engagement in December 2018.<ref>http://everything-pr.com/statement-from-petra-nemcova-and-alejandro-grimaldi/</ref>\n\nIn 2019, N\u011bmcov\u00e1 married French-Venezuelan entrepreneur Benjamin Larretche in [[Sedona, Arizona]]. They announced in September 2019 that they are expecting their first child.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Juneau |first1=Jen |last2=Leon |first2=Anya |title=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 Is Pregnant! Model, 40, Expecting First Child with Husband Benjamin Larretche |url=https://people.com/parents/petra-nemcova-pregnant-expecting-first-child-husband-benjamin-larretche/ |accessdate=20 September 2019 |magazine=People |date=September 19, 2019}}</ref> They welcomed their first child, a son, on November 15, 2019. He was born at 34 gestation and spent the first weeks of his life in the NICU.<ref> https://torontosun.com/entertainment/celebrity/supermodel-petra-nemcova-reveals-shes-a-new-mother-on-instagram/wcm/4ecda769-2333-46ea-b245-74dba0fceae3/amp</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |wikt=no |commons=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 |b=no |n=no |q=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1 |s=no |v=no |species=no |display=Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1}}\n*{{official website|http://www.petra-nemcova.com}}\n*{{Fashionmodel|name=Petra Nemcova}}\n*{{IMDb name|1023092|Petra N\u011bmcov\u00e1}}\n\n{{SI Swimsuit Cover Models}}\n{{2000\u20132009 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nemcova, Petra}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Karvin\u00e1]]\n[[Category:Czech female models]]\n[[Category:Czech television personalities]]\n[[Category:Czech women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women writers]]\n[[Category:Czech philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in Italy]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c4:c419:eb01:a19d:614e:3243:afa6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePersonal life)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petra_N%C4%9Bmcov%C3%A1"}
